  "subject": "Added internal classes to mirror models-pap classes",
  "commit_message": "Added internal classes to mirror models-pap classes\n\nInstead of creating mapper classes, decided to put the conversion methods\nwithin the classes, themselves.  This makes it less likely that someone\nwill forget to update the conversion method if fields are added or\nremoved.  Unfortunately, this meant subclassing a few of the models-pdp\nclasses (e.g., PolicyIdentXxx), to add the required conversion methods.\nOn the positive side, it means that PAP code need only use the classes\nfrom \"internal\"; classes from models-pdp can be ignored.\nRenamed some of the variables to make it less likely to confuse them.\nModified copyTo() methods to return the target object.\n\nCorrected a few IdentXxx tests.\n\nChange-Id: Ic5aa29fb46f93a90f5b97ea0fd4f6143ed7d5a32\nIssue-ID: POLICY-1542\nSigned-off-by: Jim Hahn <jrh3@att.com>\n",
